// Cryptol spec for a gapped (non-contiguous) C++ enum.
//
// `enum class Status : uint8_t { Ok = 0, NotFound = 2, Denied = 100 }`
// has only three legal discriminants: 0, 2, and 100. The
// implementation switches over all three and ends with
// `__builtin_unreachable()`, so SAW treats any other tag as a
// verification failure.
//
// Without the auto-emitted membership precondition
//
//     (r == (0 : [8])) \/ (r == (2 : [8])) \/ (r == (100 : [8]))
//
// the solver picks `r = 1` (or any other gap value) and the case
// DISPROVES. With the precondition the spec verifies: the function
// returns the discriminant unchanged for every legal tag.
//
// See bd issue `saw_spec_gen-iyh`.

classify_spec : [8] -> [32]
classify_spec r = zext r
